These were the only domains for which we have currently structures available.
For PLpro and ADRP we can run a seq alignment of all available PDBs to confirm the AA ranges (#TODO).



For SARS-CoV, more domains (the full SUD domain consisting of Macro2 + Macro3 + DPUP) were determined exactly.
These sequence were run against SARS-CoV-2 nsp3 for sequence alignments.

DPUP:
Since Ubl2 is determined exaclty and SARS-CoV has a long linker between Macro1 and Macro2, the SUD domain is checked backwards,
beginning with DPUP.
The C-term matches exaclty with the remaining sequence next to Ubl2.
The N-term has also a good alignment, leading to the final sequence of 70 AAs (in SARS-CoV: 71 AAs; seq identity = 74.29%):
	=> EVRTIKVFTTVDNINLHTQVVDMSMTYGQQFGPTYLDGADVTKIKPHNSHEGKTFYVLP

Mac3:
Same procedure as with DPUP.
C-Term is well conserved (from 19 AAs, only 1 mutation), N-term even better (first 22 AAs are identical) -> Mac3 = 125 AAs, as in SARS-CoV.

Mac2:
Not as nice conserved as Mac3. C-term is clear due to well conserved Mac3-N-term.
N-term was chosen by the aligment. No Indels occured, so length stays 138 AAs.
Mac2 of SARS-CoV-2 might be extended into the linker in N-term direction.
The resulting linker between the structurally determined Mac1 and the alignment-determined Mac2 is 33 AAs long (30 in SARS-CoV).
